data.title: About: 1938 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship Final
data.meta_description: The 1938 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship Final was the seventh All-Ireland Final and the deciding match of the 1938 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship, an inter-county camogie tournament for the top teams in Ireland. The poor state of the field militated against a fast game. Dublin won by six points.
data.text:
dbo:abstract

The 1938 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship Final was the seventh All-Ireland Final and the deciding match of the 1938 All-Ireland Senior Camogie Championship, an inter-county camogie tournament for the top teams in Ireland. The poor state of the field militated against a fast game. Dublin won by six points. (en)
